ul.li:
21. A method for conducting polymerase chain reaction (PCR) to amplify a sequence of a double-stranded target DNA molecule having a first terminus and a second terminus, which comprises:
(a) heating a sample containing the double-stranded DNA to a temperature effective to denature the DNA and thereby provide a first single strand of DNA and a second strand of DNA;
(b) contacting the denatured DNA with first and second oligonucleotide primers each comprised of a target binding sequence complementary to the first terminus of the first DNA strand and to the second terminus of the second DNA strand, respectively, wherein the first primer is a dual-purpose primer according to any of aspects 1 to 18;
(c) cooling the sample so as to allow hybridization of first and second oligonucleotide primers to the first and second strands of DNA, respectively;
(d) replicating the DNA using a DNA polymerase; and
(e) repeating the aforementioned steps (a) through (d) to provide multiple copies of the sequence of double-stranded DNA.
